<title>UK: ZENECA'S ZOMIG APPROVED FOR USE IN GERMANY.</title>
<headline>ZENECA'S ZOMIG APPROVED FOR USE IN GERMANY.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-08-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>British pharmaceuticals firm Zeneca Group Plc said on Wednesday its anti-migraine drug Zomig has been approved under new European regulatory procedures for use in Germany, Denmark and Finland.  </p>
<p>Further approvals in other markets are expected later this year and throughout 1998.</p>
<p>Zomig, on oral migraine treatment, is already available in Sweden and Britain.</p>
<p>Zeneca said that the worldwide market for migraine treatment is growing rapidly and expected to reach 1.5 billion stg by 2000.</p>
